notesStmt.note: Item is undated, but likely produced in the 19th century.
Catalog entry, 313, pasted to outside back cover.
Item cataloged from digital facsimile and existing description.

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Loose leaf codex of prayers; copied in two hands.

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 146 leaves : 220 x 175 (155 x 125) mm bound to 235 x 185 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 146; [1-146], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in West African maghribī script in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Geometric designs in red and brown on first and last pages (f. 1r, 146r); several other geometric designs throughout the text (f. 1v, 6r, 8r, 25v, 29r, 45r, 54v, 63v, 67v, 77v, 81r, 107r, 118r); rubrications in red.

binding.p: Unbound leaves between two boards with a leather strap attached to one board to wrap up the bundle.

history.provenance: Gift of John Frederick Lewis to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (inscription on bookplate inside front cover).
Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis (bookplate inside front cover).
